<p>Names ending on -mann are usually written with double-n in German.</p>
<p>As since 1942 the Ahnenerbe e.V. was part of the SS, Zimmerman(n)'s rank should be &quot;SS-Hauptsturmführer&quot; (spoken without SS-), not &quot;Hauptmann&quot;.</p>
<p>Another thing that catches my eye is the inconsistent use of &quot;&quot; and “”.</p>

